From Henry Spencer Subject Re HST Servicing Mission Scheduled for Days In article writes Also as implied by other posters why do you need to boost the orbit on this mission anyway You don't need to but it's HST like all satellites in low Earth orbit is gradually losing altitude due to air It was deployed in the highest orbit the shuttle could reach for that It needs occasional reboosting or it will eventually It has no propulsion system of its This is an excellent opportunity given that there may not be another visit for several resembles a high speed collision Henry Spencer U of Toronto Zoology between and Dick Dunn utzoo henry